cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper discusses the construction of customizable, cross-machine performance models for GPU kernels, which falls under the category of performance modeling and analysis. Therefore, cs.PF is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of symbolic gathering of performance-relevant kernel operation counts, which is related to automated reasoning (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the need for efficient modeling across multiple architectures, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of a tool for formulating mathematical models, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of benchmark kernels, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL).
